{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Renamed files appear in their own category and are not also counted as a deletion plus an addition.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between rename-status parsing and category aggregation. A pure unit test of one helper can miss cross-module double-counting bugs, but real OS/network effects are not required.","test_description":"Build an integration test around the report pipeline using fixture diff/name-status input that includes rename entries (e.g., R100 old->new). Assert the final structured report increments only `renamed` and does not increment `added`/`deleted` for the same file.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Diffs that include binary files do not cause the tool to crash; binary files are counted in the output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real binary handling failures often occur at subprocess/output decoding and git diff behavior with actual binary blobs. Mocked text fixtures can hide decode/format edge cases.","test_description":"Create a temp git repo, commit a real binary file change, run the CLI via subprocess, and assert exit code is 0 and the report includes the binary file in counts. This must execute real git and CLI process boundaries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Running the tool on a repository that has no commits yet produces an empty report rather than an error.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real git behavior for an unborn branch/no-HEAD repository, which is a subprocess and repository-state boundary.","test_description":"Initialize an empty repo with `git init` and no commits, invoke the CLI as a subprocess, and assert